You can manage **blog Custom Model Types** by altering and adding attributes to the two main Custom Model Types associated to the blog:

* Blog Instance: used to save all blog settings
* Blog Posts: stores information about all blog posts

## Example: Blog Instance Custom Model Type
`marketplace_builder/custom_model_types/blog_instance.yml`:



```yaml
{% raw %}
name: Blog Instance
custom_attributes:
- name: title
  attribute_type: string
- name: subtitle
  attribute_type: string
- name: scope
  attribute_type: string
- name: slug
  attribute_type: string
- name: facebook_app_id
  attribute_type: string
- name: enabled
  attribute_type: boolean
- name: sidebar_enabled
  attribute_type: boolean
- name: grid_view_enabled
  attribute_type: boolean
- name: tags_filter
  attribute_type: array
- name: header_logo
  attribute_type: photo
- name: header_icon
  attribute_type: photo
- name: header_image
  attribute_type: photo
  versions_configuration:
    normal:
      width: 740
      height: 300
{% endraw %}
```


## Example: Blog Post Custom Model Type
`marketplace_builder/custom_model_types/blog_post.yml`:


```yaml
{% raw %}
name: Blog Post
custom_attributes:
- name: title
  attribute_type: string
- name: content
  attribute_type: text
- name: excerpt
  attribute_type: text
- name: slug
  attribute_type: string
- name: published_at
  attribute_type: datetime
- name: hero_image
  attribute_type: photo
  html_tag: input
  versions_configuration:
    normal:
      width: 740
      height: 460
- name: tags
  attribute_type: array
- name: blog_instance_id
  attribute_type: integer
- name: author_name
  attribute_type: string
- name: author_biography
  attribute_type: text
- name: author_avatar
  attribute_type: photo
  versions_configuration:
    thumb:
      width: 100
      height: 100
{% endraw %}
```


